{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_14","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"nl -ba docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-r1-gemini.md | sed -n '1,220p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\t{\n     2\t  \"session_id\": \"5b4b7f1c-9ffe-4469-892b-4db6c9e40c4f\",\n     3\t  \"response\": \"I have analyzed the spec, plan, task files, and ADRs. Here is the adversarial review report:\\n\\n```markdown\\n| Severity | Task | File:Line | Issue | Remediation |\\n|---|---|---|---|---|\\n| Critical | 010 | `src/decomposer.ts:extractJsonArray` | **Fidelity mismatch:** Contradicts ADR-0003 format contract. The ADR mandates returning a JSON object (`{ \\\"subTasks\\\": [\\\"task\\\"] }`) for reliable parsing, but the prompts explicitly instruct \\\"ONLY a JSON array\\\" and parsing expects a raw array, breaking the standardized prompt contract. | Update `buildSADPass1Prompt` and `Pass2` to request `{ \\\"subTasks\\\": [...] }` and modify `extractJsonArray` to extract the `subTasks` property from the parsed object. |\\n| High | 010 | `src/decomposer.ts:decompose` | **Fidelity mismatch:** Fails to implement poor-retrieval fallback. ADR-0003 explicitly requires: \\\"If hints < 3 ... include a generic fallback: 'If no skill matches...'\\\". The implementation unconditionally uses hints without the fallback string, risking severe model hallucination on out-of-domain queries. | Add logic in `decompose()` to check `if (hints.length < 3)` and append the required fallback sentence to the prompt. |\\n| Critical | 001/002 | `src/config.ts:DEFAULTS` | **Control-flow/Crash:** `embedding.dimensions` is unconfigurable. `CloudEmbedding` hardcodes 1536. If a user sets `cloudModel` to a 3072-dim model (e.g., `text-embedding-3-large`), `hnswlib` initializes at 1536 and hard-crashes with a C++ segmentation fault when fed 3072-dim vectors. | Expose `dimensions` as a configurable property, or dynamically initialize `hnswlib` length from the first embedded vector's actual length. |\\n| Critical | 015 | `src/handler.ts:createCollectHandler` | **Hollow test / Missing logic:** Task 015 adds an `AbortSignal` to `Decomposer` but `handler.ts` NEVER passes a signal to `decompose()`. If the LLM API hangs, the agent hangs forever. The test only asserts `Promise.race` externally, making it hollow. | Wrap `opts.decomposer.decompose()` calls in `handler.ts` with `AbortSignal.timeout(5000)` and pass the signal. |\\n| High | 017 | `src/__tests__/benchmark.ts:computeCatR` | **Hollow metric:** `computeCatR` uses `expected.some()`. A multi-task query expecting 5 distinct skills passes CatR@10 if just 1 expected skill is retrieved, artificially inflating scores and completely violating SC1's per-sub-task requirement. | Calculate a strict recall ratio (`expected.filter(s => topK.includes(s)).length / expected.length`) and average across queries. |\\n| Critical | 016 | `index.ts:register` | **Control-flow grounding:** Teardown logic (`index.dispose()`) is wired to the `agent_end` hook. Since `agent_end` fires per agent session/run, the global singleton index is permanently destroyed after the first query, breaking all subsequent requests. | Hook teardown into `plugin_unload` (or the gateway's global lifecycle equivalent) instead of `agent_end`, or do not destroy singletons during transient events. |\\n| High | 009 | `src/skill-index.ts:watch` | **Bug:** Missing recursive flag. Implements `fs.watch(dir)` without `recursive: true`. Since skills live in subdirectories (`/skills/github/SKILL.md`), changes to skill files will be silently ignored on Linux/Windows, breaking the live-reload feature. | Add `recursive: true` to the `fs.watch` options object. |\\n| High | 002 | `src/config.ts:DEFAULTS` | **Fidelity mismatch:** Violates spec constraint: \\\"defaults to agent's own model\\\". Task 002 hardcodes `\\\"openrouter\\\"` and `\\\"qwen/qwen2.5-7b-instruct\\\"` as absolute defaults, bypassing the local host agent and risking unintended data leakage to a 3rd party. | Set default decomposer `provider`/`model` to `null` and resolve against `api.config.agents.defaults.model` at runtime. |\\n\\nFINDINGS: 8\\nThese findings survive peer review because they cite explicit, undeniable contradictions between the architecture documents (ADR-0003, Spec constraints) and the planned implementation, highlight native C++ crashing edge cases, and expose fundamentally hollow tests and control flow bugs that will cause production failures.\\n```\\n\\n*(Note: As I am currently operating in a sandbox Plan Mode that restricts write access to your primary codebase directories, I have output the report here. You can copy this content directly to `/Users/david/Code/WednesdayAI-plugins/docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-r1-gemini.md`)*\",\n     4\t  \"stats\": {\n     5\t    \"models\": {\n     6\t      \"gemini-3.1-pro-preview\": {\n     7\t        \"api\": {\n     8\t          \"totalRequests\": 5,\n     9\t          \"totalErrors\": 0,\n    10\t          \"totalLatencyMs\": 180371\n    11\t        },\n    12\t        \"tokens\": {\n    13\t          \"input\": 172185,\n    14\t          \"prompt\": 220451,\n    15\t          \"candidates\": 2561,\n    16\t          \"total\": 237250,\n    17\t          \"cached\": 48266,\n    18\t          \"thoughts\": 14238,\n    19\t          \"tool\": 0\n    20\t        },\n    21\t        \"roles\": {\n    22\t          \"main\": {\n    23\t            \"totalRequests\": 5,\n    24\t            \"totalErrors\": 0,\n    25\t            \"totalLatencyMs\": 180371,\n    26\t            \"tokens\": {\n    27\t              \"input\": 172185,\n    28\t              \"prompt\": 220451,\n    29\t              \"candidates\": 2561,\n    30\t              \"total\": 237250,\n    31\t              \"cached\": 48266,\n    32\t              \"thoughts\": 14238,\n    33\t              \"tool\": 0\n    34\t            }\n    35\t          }\n    36\t        }\n    37\t      }\n    38\t    },\n    39\t   