{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_19","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"rg -n \\\"ONLY a JSON array|extractJsonArray|buildSADPass1Prompt|subTasks|If no skill matches|hints < 3|DEFAULTS|cloudModel|dimensions|AbortSignal|decompose\\\\(|Promise.race|computeCatR|expected.some|agent_end|fs.watch|recursive|qwen/qwen2.5-7b-instruct|defaults to agent\\\" docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver docs/superpowers/specs dev-docs/adr\"","aggregated_output":"dev-docs/adr/0003-sad-prompt-contract.md:28:Output a JSON object with a \"subTasks\" array of strings.\ndev-docs/adr/0003-sad-prompt-contract.md:33:Output format: { \"subTasks\": [\"task 1\", \"task 2\", ...] }\ndev-docs/adr/0003-sad-prompt-contract.md:49:Output format: { \"subTasks\": [\"task 1\", \"task 2\", ...] }\ndev-docs/adr/0003-sad-prompt-contract.md:55:{ \"subTasks\": [\"string\", \"string\", ...] }\ndev-docs/adr/0003-sad-prompt-contract.md:58:Parsing: extract first JSON object from response → validate `subTasks` is an array of strings → max 10 sub-tasks → truncate if exceeded.\ndev-docs/adr/0003-sad-prompt-contract.md:67:5. If hints < 3 (very poor retrieval), include a generic fallback: \"If no skill matches, describe the task in general terms.\"\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-judge-codex-judges-gemini.md:9:| Critical | 010 | `src/decomposer.ts:extractJsonArray` | **Fidelity mismatch:** Contradicts ADR-0003 format contract. The ADR mandates returning a JSON object (`{ \"subTasks\": [\"task\"] }`) for reliable parsing, but the prompts explicitly instruct \"ONLY a JSON array\" and parsing expects a raw array, breaking the standardized prompt contract. | Update `buildSADPass1Prompt` and `Pass2` to request `{ \"subTasks\": [...] }` and modify `extractJsonArray` to extract the `subTasks` property from the parsed object. |\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-judge-codex-judges-gemini.md:10:| High | 010 | `src/decomposer.ts:decompose` | **Fidelity mismatch:** Fails to implement poor-retrieval fallback. ADR-0003 explicitly requires: \"If hints < 3 ... include a generic fallback: 'If no skill matches...'\". The implementation unconditionally uses hints without the fallback string, risking severe model hallucination on out-of-domain queries. | Add logic in `decompose()` to check `if (hints.length < 3)` and append the required fallback sentence to the prompt. |\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-judge-codex-judges-gemini.md:11:| Critical | 001/002 | `src/config.ts:DEFAULTS` | **Control-flow/Crash:** `embedding.dimensions` is unconfigurable. `CloudEmbedding` hardcodes 1536. If a user sets `cloudModel` to a 3072-dim model (e.g., `text-embedding-3-large`), `hnswlib` initializes at 1536 and hard-crashes with a C++ segmentation fault when fed 3072-dim vectors. | Expose `dimensions` as a configurable property, or dynamically initialize `hnswlib` length from the first embedded vector's actual length. |\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-judge-codex-judges-gemini.md:12:| Critical | 015 | `src/handler.ts:createCollectHandler` | **Hollow test / Missing logic:** Task 015 adds an `AbortSignal` to `Decomposer` but `handler.ts` NEVER passes a signal to `decompose()`. If the LLM API hangs, the agent hangs forever. The test only asserts `Promise.race` externally, making it hollow. | Wrap `opts.decomposer.decompose()` calls in `handler.ts` with `AbortSignal.timeout(5000)` and pass the signal. |\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-judge-codex-judges-gemini.md:13:| High | 017 | `src/__tests__/benchmark.ts:computeCatR` | **Hollow metric:** `computeCatR` uses `expected.some()`. A multi-task query expecting 5 distinct skills passes CatR@10 if just 1 expected skill is retrieved, artificially inflating scores and completely violating SC1's per-sub-task requirement. | Calculate a strict recall ratio (`expected.filter(s => topK.includes(s)).length / expected.length`) and average across queries. |\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-judge-codex-judges-gemini.md:14:| Critical | 016 | `index.ts:register` | **Control-flow grounding:** Teardown logic (`index.dispose()`) is wired to the `agent_end` hook. Since `agent_end` fires per agent session/run, the global singleton index is permanently destroyed after the first query, breaking all subsequent requests. | Hook teardown into `plugin_unload` (or the gateway's global lifecycle equivalent) instead of `agent_end`, or do not destroy singletons during transient events. |\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-judge-codex-judges-gemini.md:15:| High | 009 | `src/skill-index.ts:watch` | **Bug:** Missing recursive flag. Implements `fs.watch(dir)` without `recursive: true`. Since skills live in subdirectories (`/skills/github/SKILL.md`), changes to skill files will be silently ignored on Linux/Windows, breaking the live-reload feature. | Add `recursive: true` to the `fs.watch` options object. |\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-judge-codex-judges-gemini.md:16:| High | 002 | `src/config.ts:DEFAULTS` | **Fidelity mismatch:** Violates spec constraint: \"defaults to agent's own model\". Task 002 hardcodes `\"openrouter\"` and `\"qwen/qwen2.5-7b-instruct\"` as absolute defaults, bypassing the local host agent and risking unintended data leakage to a 3rd party. | Set default decomposer `provider`/`model` to `null` and resolve against `api.config.agents.defaults.model` at runtime. |\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:67:- **Skill index built at startup** — embedding index constructed in `register()`, updated on skill file changes via fs watch (debounced).\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:68:- **Separate decomposer model** — configurable, defaults to agent's own model but should support a cheaper/smaller model (e.g., Qwen2.5-7B, gpt-4o-mini) to reduce the decomposition cost overhead.\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:97:- Watched for changes via fs.watch (debounced rebuild)\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:139:  ├─ Pass 1: Decomposer.decompose(query, hints=null)\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:147:  ├─ Pass 2 (SAD): Decomposer.decompose(query, hints=hintSet)\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:195:        subTasks: [\"download CSV\", \"run analysis\"],\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:196:        decomposerModel: \"qwen/qwen2.5-7b-instruct\",\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:212:        \"model\": \"qwen/qwen2.5-7b-instruct\",\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:221:        \"cloudModel\": \"text-embedding-3-small\", // cloud model (OpenAI)\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:244:  readonly dimensions: number;\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:284:The prompt contract is: `{ subTasks: string[] }` — a JSON array of one-skill-per-task strings. This is intentionally minimal to keep parsing deterministic.\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:315:| `Decomposer` | Parse valid JSON response, handle malformed JSON, handle empty/missing subTasks field, Pass-1 no hints, Pass-2 with hints |\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:319:| `EmbeddingBackend` (×3) | Local: loads model, embeds text, correct dimensions. Cloud: sends correct API request format. Custom: handles endpoint URL and auth. |\ndev-docs/adr/0004-in-memory-index-no-persistence.md:18:Build the skill index in-memory at plugin startup. Do not persist to disk. Rebuild on any skill file change (fs.watch, debounced).\ndev-docs/adr/0004-in-memory-index-no-persistence.md:45:- **Positive:** Dimension-agnostic — if the user switches embedding backends (384-dim → 1536-dim), the index rebuilds automatically with the new dimensions. A persisted index would need dimension-aware invalidation.\ndev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md:27:  readonly dimensions: number;\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-r1-gemini.raw.log:3:  \"response\": \"I have analyzed the spec, plan, task files, and ADRs. Here is the adversarial review report:\\n\\n```markdown\\n| Severity | Task | File:Line | Issue | Remediation |\\n|---|---|---|---|---|\\n| Critical | 010 | `src/decomposer.ts:extractJsonArray` | **Fidelity mismatch:** Contradicts ADR-0003 format contract. The ADR mandates returning a JSON object (`{ \\\"subTasks\\\": [\\\"task\\\"] }`) for reliable parsing, but the prompts explicitly instruct \\\"ONLY a JSON array\\\" and parsing expects a raw array, breaking the standardized prompt contract. | Update `buildSADPass1Prompt` and `Pass2` to request `{ \\\"subTasks\\\": [...] }` and modify `extractJsonArray` to extract the `subTasks` property from the parsed object. |\\n| High | 010 | `src/decomposer.ts:decompose` | **Fidelity mismatch:** Fails to implement poor-retrieval fallback. ADR-0003 explicitly requires: \\\"If hints < 3 ... include a generic fallback: 'If no skill matches...'\\\". The implementation unconditionally uses hints without the fallback string, risking severe model hallucination on out-of-domain queries. | Add logic in `decompose()` to check `if (hints.length < 3)` and append the required fallback sentence to the prompt. |\\n| Critical | 001/002 | `src/config.ts:DEFAULTS` | **Control-flow/Crash:** `embedding.dimensions` is unconfigurable. `CloudEmbedding` hardcodes 1536. If a user sets `cloudModel` to a 3072-dim model (e.g., `text-embedding-3-large`), `hnswlib` initializes at 1536 and hard-crashes with a C++ segmentation fault when fed 3072-dim vectors. | Expose `dimensions` as a configurable property, or dynamically initialize `hnswlib` length from the first embedded vector's actual length. |\\n| Critical | 015 | `src/handler.ts:createCollectHandler` | **Hollow test / Missing logic:** Task 015 adds an `AbortSignal` to `Decomposer` but `handler.ts` NEVER passes a signal to `decompose()`. If the LLM API hangs, the agent hangs forever. The test only asserts `Promise.race` externally, making it hollow. | Wrap `opts.decomposer.decompose()` calls in `handler.ts` with `AbortSignal.timeout(5000)` and pass the signal. |\\n| High | 017 | `src/__tests__/benchmark.ts:computeCatR` | **Hollow metric:** `computeCatR` uses `expected.some()`. A multi-task query expecting 5 distinct skills passes CatR@10 if just 1 expected skill is retrieved, artificially inflating scores and completely violating SC1's per-sub-task requirement. | Calculate a strict recall ratio (`expected.filter(s => topK.includes(s)).length / expected.length`) and average across queries. |\\n| Critical | 016 | `index.ts:register` | **Control-flow grounding:** Teardown logic (`index.dispose()`) is wired to the `agent_end` hook. Since `agent_end` fires per agent session/run, the global singleton index is permanently destroyed after the first query, breaking all subsequent requests. | Hook teardown into `plugin_unload` (or the gateway's global lifecycle equivalent) instead of `agent_end`, or do not destroy singletons during transient events. |\\n| High | 009 | `src/skill-index.ts:watch` | **Bug:** Missing recursive flag. Implements `fs.watch(dir)` without `recursive: true`. Since skills live in subdirectories (`/skills/github/SKILL.md`), changes to skill files will be silently ignored on Linux/Windows, breaking the live-reload feature. | Add `recursive: true` to the `fs.watch` options object. |\\n| High | 002 | `src/config.ts:DEFAULTS` | **Fidelity mismatch:** Violates spec constraint: \\\"defaults to agent's own model\\\". Task 002 hardcodes `\\\"openrouter\\\"` and `\\\"qwen/qwen2.5-7b-instruct\\\"` as absolute defaults, bypassing the local host agent and risking unintended data leakage to a 3rd party. | Set default decomposer `provider`/`model` to `null` and resolve against `api.config.agents.defaults.model` at runtime. |\\n\\nFINDINGS: 8\\nThese findings survive peer review because they cite explicit, undeniable contradictions between the architecture documents (ADR-0003, Spec constraints) and the planned implementation, highlight native C++ crashing edge cases, and expose fundamentally hollow tests and control flow bugs that will cause production failures.\\n```\\n\\n*(Note: As I am currently operating in a sandbox Plan Mode that restricts write access to your primary codebase directories, I have output the report here. You can copy this content directly to `/Users/david/Code/WednesdayAI-plugins/docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-r1-gemini.md`)*\",\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/011-retriever.md:120:  retrieve(subTasks: string[]): Promise<SearchResult[]>;\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/011-retriever.md:121:  buildHintSet(subTasks: string[]): Promise<HintEntry[]>;\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/011-retriever.md:129:    async retrieve(subTasks: string[]): Promise<SearchResult[]> {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/011-retriever.md:130:      if (subTasks.length === 0) return [];\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/011-retriever.md:134:      for (const task of subTasks) {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/011-retriever.md:147:    async buildHintSet(subTasks: string[]): Promise<HintEntry[]> {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/011-retriever.md:148:      if (subTasks.length === 0) return [];\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/011-retriever.md:152:      for (const task of subTasks) {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/011-retriever.md:153:        const results = await index.search(task, Math.min(topK, Math.ceil(hintSize / subTasks.length)));\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/011-retriever.md:174:- `retrieve()` or `buildHintSet()` mutate the input subTasks array\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/018-integration-tests.md:178:- Plugin registers hooks other than `context.collect` (other than the lifecycle `agent_end` from task 016)\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/017-benchmark.md:420:function computeCatR(retrieved: SearchResult[], expected: string[], k: number): boolean {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/017-benchmark.md:422:  return expected.some((skill) => topK.includes(skill));\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/017-benchmark.md:433:  decomposer: { decompose: (query: string, hints?: HintEntry[]) => Promise<{ subTasks: string[]; pass: number }> };\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/017-benchmark.md:434:  retriever: { retrieve: (subTasks: string[]) => Promise<SearchResult[]> };\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/017-benchmark.md:444:    const pass1Result = await opts.decomposer.decompose(q.query);\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/017-benchmark.md:445:    const retrieved = await opts.retriever.retrieve(pass1Result.subTasks);\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/017-benchmark.md:449:    const da = computeDA(pass1Result.subTasks.length, q.expectedSubtasks);\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/017-benchmark.md:455:      catR10: computeCatR(retrieved, q.expectedSkills, 10),\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/017-benchmark.md:456:      catR1: computeCatR(retrieved, q.expectedSkills, 1),\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/017-benchmark.md:460:      subTaskCount: pass1Result.subTasks.length,\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/010-decomposer.md:24:const buildSADPass1Prompt = (query: string) => `PASS 1: ${query}`;\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/010-decomposer.md:36:        buildSADPass1Prompt,\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/010-decomposer.md:44:  describe(\"decompose() — Pass 1 (no hints)\", () => {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/010-decomposer.md:49:        model: \"qwen/qwen2.5-7b-instruct\",\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/010-decomposer.md:60:      const result = await decomposer.decompose(\"download this dataset and analyze it\");\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/010-decomposer.md:61:      expect(result.subTasks).toEqual([\"download CSV from URL\", \"run statistica