mposer protocol. | Change tests, prompts, and parser to emit/extract `{ \\\"subTasks\\\": [...] }`; keep array-only parsing only as backward-compatible fallback if explicitly allowed. |\\n| High | 004 | `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:270-276`; `dev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md:22-31`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-2/004-embedding-types.md:11`, `:65-71` | Task 004 creates the `EmbeddingBackend` interface but marks `irreversible: false`, contradicting D2/ADR-0002’s irreversible interface-contract decision. | Mark task 004 `irreversible: true` and cite ADR-0002 in the task header or body. |\\n| High | 009 | `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-3/009-index-rebuild.md:141-160` | The proposed `watch()` calls `import(\\\"node:fs\\\").watch(...)` without awaiting/importing `watch`, never assigns `this.watcher`, then returns `this.watcher`; the method returns `null` and/or typechecks incorrectly instead of starting a watcher. | Use `import { existsSync, watch } from \\\"node:fs\\\"` at top level, return `null` when the dir is missing, assign `this.watcher = watch(...)`, and close any previous watcher before replacing it. |\\n| High | 015 | `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-6/015-error-resilience.md:24-42`, `:106-119`, `:179-195` | The timeout tests are hollow: both race the unresolved implementation against an external already/soon-resolving fallback, so they pass even if `handler()`/`decompose()` never implements timeout. The change only threads an optional `signal`; no handler creates an `AbortController` or deadline. | Add a real timeout option, create/abort an `AbortController` in the handler/decomposer path, await the actual handler promise under fake timers, and assert it resolves `{}` plus passes an aborted signal to fetch. |\\n| Medium | 016/018 | `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-6/016-lifecycle.md:130-136`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/018-integration-tests.md:87-93`, `:174-179` | Task 016 adds a second `api.on(\\\"agent_end\\\", ...)` hook, but task 018 still asserts `api.on` was called exactly once. Its own STOP trigger later allows `agent_end`, so the integration task conflicts with its dependency. | Update task 018 to assert only allowed hook names are registered: `context.collect` and `agent_end`; do not use `toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1)`. |\\n| High | 017 | `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:44-47`, `:61-62`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/017-benchmark.md:432-491`, `:503-509` | The benchmark file only exports `runBenchmark`; it does not load the 50-query fixture, instantiate real or mock components, print rates, or fail when CatR@10/DA thresholds miss. The Done command can exit 0 without proving SC1, SC2, or SC7. | Add a CLI entrypoint that loads `benchmark-queries.json`, runs the real configured pipeline or deterministic benchmark mocks, prints summary, and exits non-zero unless `catR10Rate >= 0.65`, `daExactRate >= 0.60`, and latency thresholds pass. |\\n| Medium | 012 | `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:174-180`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/012-context-injector.md:49-52`, `:160-163` | The spec’s contribution source is `\\\"plugin-skillweaver\\\"`, but task 012 tests and implements `source: \\\"skillweaver\\\"`. Downstream diagnostics/filtering by source will not match the frozen contract. | Align task 012 and dependent tests to `source: \\\"plugin-skillweaver\\\"` or amend the spec before implementation. |\\n| Medium | 018 | `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:53-56`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/018-integration-tests.md:70-84`, `:87-93` | The SC4 cache test sends `\\\"hi\\\"`, which is below `minQueryLength`, then only checks `systemPrompt` if the result is non-empty; it passes if no injection ever occurs. The SC5 slash-command test only checks no `before_tool_call` hook, not that `/github` or `/weather` still resolve. | Use a long query with mocked re