n-skillweaver/phase-5/013-collect-handler.md:250:      let subTasks: string[];\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/013-collect-handler.md:252:      if (opts.sadEnabled && pass1Result.subTasks.length > 0) {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/013-collect-handler.md:253:        const hints = await opts.retriever.buildHintSet(pass1Result.subTasks);\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/013-collect-handler.md:255:          const pass2Result = await opts.decomposer.decompose(text, hints);\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/013-collect-handler.md:256:          subTasks = pass2Result.subTasks.length > 0 ? pass2Result.subTasks : pass1Result.subTasks;\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/013-collect-handler.md:258:          subTasks = pass1Result.subTasks;\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/013-collect-handler.md:261:        subTasks = pass1Result.subTasks;\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/013-collect-handler.md:264:      const results = await opts.retriever.retrieve(subTasks);\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/013-collect-handler.md:265:      const contribution = formatSkillContext(results, text, subTasks, opts.decomposerModel);\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/013-collect-handler.md:269:          subTasks: subTasks.length,\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-judge-gemini-judges-codex.md:14:| Critical | 010 | Spec, ADR-0003, task 010 | SAD contract is JSON object `{ subTasks: string[] }` but task 010 prompts for and parses a bare JSON array. | Change tests, prompts, and parser to emit/extract `{ \"subTasks\": [...] }`. |\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-judge-gemini-judges-codex.md:18:| Medium | 016/018 | Task 016 lines 130-136; task 018 lines 87-93, 174-179 | Task 016 adds second `agent_end` hook, but task 018 still asserts `api.on` called exactly once. | Update task 018 to assert only allowed hook names are registered. |\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-r1-gemini.md:3:  \"response\": \"I have analyzed the spec, plan, task files, and ADRs. Here is the adversarial review report:\\n\\n```markdown\\n| Severity | Task | File:Line | Issue | Remediation |\\n|---|---|---|---|---|\\n| Critical | 010 | `src/decomposer.ts:extractJsonArray` | **Fidelity mismatch:** Contradicts ADR-0003 format contract. The ADR mandates returning a JSON object (`{ \\\"subTasks\\\": [\\\"task\\\"] }`) for reliable parsing, but the prompts explicitly instruct \\\"ONLY a JSON array\\\" and parsing expects a raw array, breaking the standardized prompt contract. | Update `buildSADPass1Prompt` and `Pass2` to request `{ \\\"subTasks\\\": [...] }` and modify `extractJsonArray` to extract the `subTasks` property from the parsed object. |\\n| High | 010 | `src/decomposer.ts:decompose` | **Fidelity mismatch:** Fails to implement poor-retrieval fallback. ADR-0003 explicitly requires: \\\"If hints < 3 ... include a generic fallback: 'If no skill matches...'\\\". The implementation unconditionally uses hints without the fallback string, risking severe model hallucination on out-of-domain queries. | Add logic in `decompose()` to check `if (hints.length < 3)` and append the required fallback sentence to the prompt. |\\n| Critical | 001/002 | `src/config.ts:DEFAULTS` | **Control-flow/Crash:** `embedding.dimensions` is unconfigurable. `CloudEmbedding` hardcodes 1536. If a user sets `cloudModel` to a 3072-dim model (e.g., `text-embedding-3-large`), `hnswlib` initializes at 1536 and hard-crashes with a C++ segmentation fault when fed 3072-dim vectors. | Expose `dimensions` as a configurable property, or dynamically initialize `hnswlib` length from the first embedded vector's actual length. |\\n| Critical | 015 | `src/handler.ts:createCollectHandler` | **Hollow test / Missing logic:** Task 015 adds an `AbortSignal` to `Decomposer` but `handler.ts` NEVER passes a signal to `decompose()`. If the LLM API hangs, the agent hangs forever. The test only asserts `Promise.race` externally, making it hollow. | Wrap `opts.decomposer.decompose()` calls in `handler.ts` with `AbortSignal.timeout(5000)` and pass the signal. |\\n| High | 017 | `src/__tests__/benchmark.ts:computeCatR` | **Hollow metric:** `computeCatR` uses `expected.some()`. A multi-task query expecting 5 distinct skills passes CatR@10 if just 1 expected skill is retrieved, artificially inflating scores and completely violating SC1's per-sub-task requirement. | Calculate a strict recall ratio (`expected.filter(s => topK.includes(s)).length / expected.length`) and average across queries. |\\n| Critical | 016 | `index.ts:register` | **Control-flow grounding:** Teardown logic (`index.dispose()`) is wired to the `agent_end` hook. Since `agent_end` fires per agent session/run, the global singleton index is permanently destroyed after the first query, breaking all subsequent requests. | Hook teardown into `plugin_unload` (or the gateway's global lifecycle equivalent) instead of `agent_end`, or do not destroy singletons during transient events. |\\n| High | 009 | `src/skill-index.ts:watch` | **Bug:** Missing recursive flag. Implements `fs.watch(dir)` without `recursive: true`. Since skills live in subdirectories (`/skills/github/SKILL.md`), changes to skill files will be silently ignored on Linux/Windows, breaking the live-reload feature. | Add `recursive: true` to the `fs.watch` options object. |\\n| High | 002 | `src/config.ts:DEFAULTS` | **Fidelity mismatch:** Violates spec constraint: \\\"defaults to agent's own model\\\". Task 002 hardcodes `\\\"openrouter\\\"` and `\\\"qwen/qwen2.5-7b-instruct\\\"` as absolute defaults, bypassing the local host agent and risking unintended data leakage to a 3rd party. | Set default decomposer `provider`/`model` to `null` and resolve against `api.config.agents.defaults.model` at runtime. |\\n\\nFINDINGS: 8\\nThese findings survive peer review because they cite explicit, undeniable contradictions between the architecture documents (ADR-0003, Spec constraints) and the planned implementation, highlight native C++ crashing edge cases, and expose fundamentally hollow tests and control flow bugs that will cause production failures.\\n```\\n\\n*(Note: As I am currently operating in a sandbox Plan Mode that restricts write access to your primary codebase directories, I have output the report here. You can copy this content directly to `/Users/david/Code/WednesdayAI-plugins/docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-r1-gemini.md`)*\",\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-r1-codex.md:10:| Critical | 010 | `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:278-285`; `dev-docs/adr/0003-sad-prompt-contract.md:28`, `:33`, `:55`, `:58`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/010-decomposer.md:224-240`, `:247-269` | The irreversible SAD contract is JSON object `{ subTasks: string[] }`, but task 010 prompts for and parses a bare JSON array. This breaks the frozen decomposer protocol. | Change tests, prompts, and parser to emit/extract `{ \"subTasks\": [...] }`; keep array-only parsing only as backward-compatible fallback if explicitly allowed. |\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-r1-codex.md:13:| High | 015 | `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-6/015-error-resilience.md:24-42`, `:106-119`, `:179-195` | The timeout tests are hollow: both race the unresolved implementation against an external already/soon-resolving fallback, so they pass even if `handler()`/`decompose()` never implements timeout. The change only threads an optional `signal`; no handler creates an `AbortController` or deadline. | Add a real timeout option, create/abort an `AbortController` in the handler/decomposer path, await the actual handler promise under fake timers, and assert it resolves `{}` plus passes an aborted signal to fetch. |\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-r1-codex.md:14:| Medium | 016/018 | `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-6/016-lifecycle.md:130-136`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/018-integration-tests.md:87-93`, `:174-179` | Task 016 adds a second `api.on(\"agent_end\", ...)` hook, but task 018 still asserts `api.on` was called exactly once. Its own STOP trigger later allows `agent_end`, so the integration task conflicts with its dependency. | Update task 018 to assert only allowed hook names are registered: `context.collect` and `agent_end`; do not use `toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1)`. |\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/001-plugin-scaffold.md:127:            \"default\": \"qwen/qwen2.5-7b-instruct\",\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/001-plugin-scaffold.md:167:          \"cloudModel\": {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/014-register-wiring.md:158:        model: config.embedding.cloudModel,\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/012-context-injector.md:67:      \"qwen/qwen2.5-7b-instruct\",\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/012-context-injector.md:70:    expect(result.prependContext![0].metadata!.decomposerModel).toBe(\"qwen/qwen2.5-7b-instruct\");\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/012-context-injector.md:98:    expect(result.prependContext![0].metadata!.subTasks).toHaveLength(10);\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/012-context-injector.md:133:  subTasks: string[],\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/012-context-injector.md:151:  if (subTasks.length > 0) {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/012-context-injector.md:153:    for (const task of subTasks) {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/012-context-injector.md:168:      subTasks,\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
