{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_21","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"nl -ba docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/017-benchmark.md | sed -n '400,520p'; nl -ba docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-3/009-index-rebuild.md | sed -n '1,220p'; nl -ba docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/002-config-schema.md | sed -n '1,220p'\"","aggregated_output":"   400\t  catR10: boolean;\n   401\t  catR1: boolean;\n   402\t  daExact: boolean;\n   403\t  daPlusMinus1: boolean;\n   404\t  latencyMs: number;\n   405\t  subTaskCount: number;\n   406\t  retrievedCount: number;\n   407\t  pass: number;\n   408\t}\n   409\t\n   410\tinterface BenchmarkSummary {\n   411\t  totalQueries: number;\n   412\t  catR10Rate: number;\n   413\t  catR1Rate: number;\n   414\t  daExactRate: number;\n   415\t  daPlusMinus1Rate: number;\n   416\t  avgLatencyMs: number;\n   417\t  byDifficulty: Record<string, Omit<BenchmarkSummary, \"byDifficulty\" | \"totalQueries\">>;\n   418\t}\n   419\t\n   420\tfunction computeCatR(retrieved: SearchResult[], expected: string[], k: number): boolean {\n   421\t  const topK = retrieved.slice(0, k).map((s) => s.name);\n   422\t  return expected.some((skill) => topK.includes(skill));\n   423\t}\n   424\t\n   425\tfunction computeDA(actualSubTasks: number, expectedSubTasks: number): { exact: boolean; plusMinus1: boolean } {\n   426\t  return {\n   427\t    exact: actualSubTasks === expectedSubTasks,\n   428\t    plusMinus1: Math.abs(actualSubTasks - expectedSubTasks) <= 1,\n   429\t  };\n   430\t}\n   431\t\n   432\texport async function runBenchmark(opts: {\n   433\t  decomposer: { decompose: (query: string, hints?: HintEntry[]) => Promise<{ subTasks: string[]; pass: number }> };\n   434\t  retriever: { retrieve: (subTasks: string[]) => Promise<SearchResult[]> };\n   435\t  queries: BenchmarkQuery[];\n   436\t  name?: string;\n   437\t}): Promise<{ results: BenchmarkResult[]; summary: BenchmarkSummary }> {\n   438\t  const results: BenchmarkResult[] = [];\n   439\t  let totalLatency = 0;\n   440\t\n   441\t  for (const q of opts.queries) {\n   442\t    const start = Date.now();\n   443\t\n   444\t    const pass1Result = await opts.decomposer.decompose(q.query);\n   445\t    const retrieved = await opts.retriever.retrieve(pass1Result.subTasks);\n   446\t    const latencyMs = Date.now() - start;\n   447\t    totalLatency += latencyMs;\n   448\t\n   449\t    const da = computeDA(pass1Result.subTasks.length, q.expectedSubtasks);\n   450\t\n   451\t    results.push({\n   452\t      id: q.id,\n   453\t      difficulty: q.difficulty,\n   454\t      query: q.query,\n   455\t      catR10: computeCatR(retrieved, q.expectedSkills, 10),\n   456\t      catR1: computeCatR(retrieved, q.expectedSkills, 1),\n   457\t      daExact: da.exact,\n   458\t      daPlusMinus1: da.plusMinus1,\n   459\t      latencyMs,\n   460\t      subTaskCount: pass1Result.subTasks.length,\n   461\t      retrievedCount: retrieved.length,\n   462\t      pass: pass1Result.pass,\n   463\t    });\n   464\t  }\n   465\t\n   466\t  const computeRates = (subset: BenchmarkResult[]) => {\n   467\t    const n = subset.length;\n   468\t    if (n === 0) return { catR10Rate: 0, catR1Rate: 0, daExactRate: 0, daPlusMinus1Rate: 0, avgLatencyMs: 0 };\n   469\t    return {\n   470\t      catR10Rate: subset.filter((r) => r.catR10).length / n,\n   471\t      catR1Rate: subset.filter((r) => r.catR1).length / n,\n   472\t      daExactRate: subset.filter((r) => r.daExact).length / n,\n   473\t      daPlusMinus1Rate: subset.filter((r) => r.daPlusMinus1).length / n,\n   474\t      avgLatencyMs: subset.reduce((s, r) => s + r.latencyMs, 0) / n,\n   475\t    };\n   476\t  };\n   477\t\n   478\t  const byDifficulty: Record<string, Omit<BenchmarkSummary, \"byDifficulty\" | \"totalQueries\">> = {};\n   479\t  for (const diff of [\"easy\", \"medium\", \"hard\"]) {\n   480\t    byDifficulty[diff] = computeRates(results.filter((r) => r.difficulty === diff));\n   481\t  }\n   482\t\n   483\t  return {\n   484\t    results,\n   485\t    summary: {\n   486\t      totalQueries: results.length,\n   487\t      ...computeRates(results),\n   488\t      byDifficulty,\n   489\t    },\n   490\t  };\n   491\t}\n   492\t```\n   493\t\n   494\t## Allowed moves\n   495\t\n   496\tCreate exactly the benchmark file, the fixtures JSON, and add them to `files:`. No other changes. The benchmark is run manually (`npx tsx src/__tests__/benchmark.ts`) — it is not a vitest test. It requires a real decomposer and retriever (or mocks configured for the specific benchmark fixture).\n   497\t\n   498\t## STOP triggers\n   499\t\n   500\t- `expectedSkills` references a skill name not in WednesdayAI's bundled skill list (verify against the actual skill names)\n   501\t- CatR calculation is inverted (should be: expected ∩ retrieved, not retrieved ∩ expected)\n   502\t\n   503\t## Manual verification (record in decisions-ledger)\n   504\t\n   505\tRun `npx tsx src/__tests__/benchmark.ts` with mocks or real components. Verify: `summary.catR10Rate >= 0.65` and `summary.daExactRate >= 0.60` from the output. Record actual rates in decisions-ledger.\n   506\t\n   507\t## Done when\n   508\t\n   509\t`WAI_TYPECHECK_CMD=\"cd extensions/skillweaver && pnpm exec tsc --noEmit\" WAI_TEST_CMD=\"cd extensions/skillweaver && npx tsx src/__tests__/benchmark.ts\" bash ~/.claude/wai/scripts/task-gate.sh plugin-skillweaver 017` exits 0     1\t---\n     2\tid: \"009\"\n     3\tphase: 3\n     4\ttitle: Add debounced fs.watch rebuild to SkillIndex for live skill file changes\n     5\tstatus: ready\n     6\tdepends_on: [\"008\"]\n     7\tparallel: false\n     8\tconflicts_with: []\n     9\tfiles:\n    10\t  - extensions/skillweaver/src/skill-index.ts\n    11\tirreversible: false\n    12\tscope_test: \"extensions/skillweaver/src/skill-index.test.ts\"\n    13\tallowed_change: edit\n    14\tcovers_criteria: [SC1]\n    15\t---\n    16\t## Failing test (write first)\n    17\t\n    18\tAdd these tests to `extensions/skillweaver/src/skill-index.test.ts`:\n    19\t\n    20\t```ts\n    21\t// ==== Add to existing describe(\"SkillIndex\", () => { ... }) block ====\n    22\t\n    23\t  describe(\"watch() / rebuild\", () => {\n    24\t    it(\"watch() starts a file watcher\", async () => {\n    25\t      const index = new SkillIndex(mockBackend);\n    26\t      await index.build(sampleSkills);\n    27\t      const watcher = index.watch(\"/tmp/skills\", () => [...sampleSkills]);\n    28\t      expect(watcher).toBeDefined();\n    29\t      expect(watcher?.close).toBeDefined();\n    30\t      watcher?.close();\n    31\t    });\n    32\t\n    33\t    it(\"returns null for non-existent dir\", () => {\n    34\t      const index = new SkillIndex(mockBackend);\n    35\t      const watcher = index.watch(\"/nonexistent/path\", () => []);\n    36\t      expect(watcher).toBeNull();\n    37\t    });\n    38\t\n    39\t    it(\"unwatch() closes the watcher\", async () => {\n    40\t      const index = new SkillIndex(mockBackend);\n    41\t      await index.build(sampleSkills);\n    42\t      index.watch(\"/tmp/skills\", () => [...sampleSkills]);\n    43\t      const closed = index.unwatch();\n    44\t      expect(closed).toBe(true);\n    45\t    });\n    46\t\n    47\t    it(\"unwatch() returns false when no watcher active\", () => {\n    48\t      const index = new SkillIndex(mockBackend);\n    49\t      expect(index.unwatch()).toBe(false);\n    50\t    });\n    51\t\n    52\t    it(\"second watch() closes the first watcher\", async () => {\n    53\t      const index = new SkillIndex(mockBackend);\n    54\t      await index.build(sampleSkills);\n    55\t      const w1 = index.watch(\"/tmp/skills\", () => [...sampleSkills]);\n    56\t      const w2 = index.watch(\"/tmp/skills\", () => [...sampleSkills]);\n    57\t      expect(w1?.close).toBeDefined();\n    58\t      expect(w2?.close).toBeDefined();\n    59\t      w2?.close();\n    60\t    });\n    61\t\n    62\t    it(\"calls skillProvider and rebuilds after debounce\", async () => {\n    63\t      vi.useFakeTimers();\n    64\t      const index = new SkillIndex(mockBackend);\n    65\t      await index.build(sampleSkills);\n    66\t\n    67\t      const freshSkills: SkillEntry[] = [\n    68\t        { name: \"github\", description: \"Updated github skill\", location: \"/x\", source: \"bundled\" },\n    69\t      ];\n    70\t\n    71\t      let callCount = 0;\n    72\t      const provider = () => {\n    73\t        callCount++;\n    74\t        return callCount === 1 ? sampleSkills : freshSkills;\n    75\t      };\n    76\t\n    77\t      const watcher = index.watch(\"/tmp/skills\", provider, { debounceMs: 100 });\n    78\t      expect(watcher).toBeDefined();\n    79\t\n    80\t      // Trigger a change event\n    81\t      (watcher as unknown as { _emit: (e: string, f: string) => void })._emit?.(\"change\", \"somefile.md\") ??\n    82\t        watcher?.emit?.(\"change\", \"somefile.md\");\n    83\t\n    84\t      // Fast-forward past debounce\n    85\t      await vi.advanceTimersToNextTimerAsync();\n    86\t      await vi.runAllTimersAsync();\n    87\t\n    88\t      expect(callCount).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(1);\n    89\t\n    90\t      watcher?.close();\n    91\t      vi.useRealTimers();\n    92\t    });\n    93\t  });\n    94\t```\n    95\t\n    96\t## Change\n    97\t\n    98\t**File:** `extensions/skillweaver/src/skill-index.ts`\n    99\t**Anchor:** `SkillIndex` class — add watch/unwatch fields + method after the existing fields/methods\n   100\t**Before:**\n   101\t```ts\n   102\texport class SkillIndex {\n   103\t  private backend: EmbeddingBackend;\n   104\t  private skills = new Map<string, IndexedSkill>();\n   105\t  private index: Awaited<ReturnType<typeof this.createHnsw>> | null = null;\n   106\t\n   107\t  constructor(backend: EmbeddingBackend) {\n   108\t    this.backend = backend;\n   109\t  }\n   110\t```\n   111\t**After:**\n   112\t```ts\n   113\texport interface WatchOptions {\n   114\t  debounceMs?: number;\n   115\t}\n   116\t\n   117\texport class SkillIndex {\n   118\t  private backend: EmbeddingBackend;\n   119\t  private skills = new Map<string, IndexedSkill>();\n   120\t  private index: Awaited<ReturnType<typeof this.createHnsw>> | null = null;\n   121\t  private watcher: import(\"node:fs\").FSWatcher | null = null;\n   122\t  private rebuildTimer: ReturnType<typeof setTimeout> | null = null;\n   123\t  private watchDir: string | null = null;\n   124\t\n   125\t  constructor(backend: EmbeddingBackend) {\n   126\t    this.backend = backend;\n   127\t  }\n   128\t```\n   129\t\n   130\tAnd add these methods before `dispose()`:\n   131\t\n   132\t**Before:**\n   133\t```ts\n   134\t  dispose(): void {\n   135\t    this.index = null;\n   136\t    this.skills.clear();\n   137\t  }\n   138\t```\n   139\t**After:**\n   140\t```ts\n   141\t  watch(\n   142\t    dir: string,\n   143\t    skillProvider: () => SkillEntry[],\n   144\t    opts: WatchOptions = {},\n   145\t  ): import(\"node:fs\").FSWatcher | null {\n   146\t    import(\"node:fs\").watch(dir, { persistent: false }, (_event, filename) => {\n   147\t      if (!filename?.endsWith(\".md\")) return;\n   148\t      if (this.rebuildTimer) clearTimeout(this.rebuildTimer);\n   149\t      this.rebuildTimer = setTimeout(async () => {\n   150\t        try {\n   151\t          const entries = skillProvider();\n   152\t          await this.build(entries);\n   153\t          log.info(`index rebuilt after fs change: ${filename}`);\n   154\t        } catch (err) {\n   155\t          log.error(\"rebuild failed\", { error: String(err) });\n   156\t        }\n   157\t      }, opts.debounceMs ?? 2000);\n   158\t    });\n   159\t    return this.watcher;\n   160\t  }\n   161\t\n   162\t  unwatch(): boolean {\n   163\t    if (this.rebuildTimer) {\n   164\t      clearTimeout(this.rebuildTimer);\n   165\t      this.rebuildTimer = null;\n   166\t    }\n   167\t    if (this.watcher) {\n   168\t      this.watcher.close();\n   169\t      this.watcher = null;\n   170\t      return true;\n   171\t    }\n   172\t    return false;\n   173\t  }\n   174\t\n   175\t  dispose(): void {\n   176\t    this.unwatch();\n   177\t    this.index = null;\n   178\t    this.skills.clear();\n   179\t  }\n   180\t```\n   181\t\n   182\t## Allowed moves\n   183\t\n   184\tOnly modify `extensions/skillweaver/src/skill-index.ts`: add the watcher field + `watch()` + `unwatch()` methods, update `dispose()` to call `unwatch()`. Add the test cases above to the existing test file. Do NOT change any existing method signatures. Do NOT add new files.\n   185\t\n   186\t## STOP triggers\n   187\t\n   188\t- `watch()` method changes the return type of `build()` or `search()`\n   189\t- `dispose()` is called without cleaning up the watcher\n   190\t- The `import(\"node:fs\")` dynamic import causes a type error — if so, use `import { watch } from \"node:fs\"` as a top-level import instead\n   191\t\n   192\t## Done when\n   193\t\n   194\t`WAI_TYPECHECK_CMD=\"cd extensions/skillweaver && pnpm exec tsc --noEmit\" WAI_TEST_CMD=\"cd extensions/skillweaver && npx vitest run src/skill-index.test.ts\" bash ~/.claude/wai/scripts/task-gate.sh plugin-skillweaver 009` exits 0     1\t---\n     2\tid: \"002\"\n     3\tphase: 1\n     4\ttitle: Create config schema resolver, validator, and skills-mode checker\n     5\tstatus: ready\n     6\tdepends_on: [\"001\"]\n     7\tparallel: false\n     8\tconflicts_with: []\n     9\tfiles:\n    10\t  - extensions/skillweaver/src/config.ts\n    11\tirreversible: false\n    12\tscope_test: \"extensions/skillweaver/src/config.test.ts\"\n    13\tallowed_change: create\n    14\tcovers_criteria: [SC6]\n    15\t---\n    16\t## Failing test (write first)\n    17\t\n    18\tCreate `extensions/skillweaver/src/config.test.ts`:\n    19\t\n    20\t```ts\n    21\timport { describe, it, expect } from \"vitest\";\n    22\timport { resolveConfig, checkSkillsMode, validateConfig } from \".