{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_23","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"rg -n \\\"agent_end|plugin_unload|context.collect|OpenClawPluginApi|api.on\\\\(\\\" README.md docs dev-docs .gitignore\"","aggregated_output":"dev-docs/workstreams/plugin-skillweaver/README.md:26:- [ADR-0001](/dev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md) — `context.collect` hook for skill injection\ndev-docs/workstreams/plugin-skillweaver/README.md:34:| 0001 | `context.collect` hook for skill injection | accepted |\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:23:This plugin brings SkillWeaver to WednesdayAI as a community extension, serving dual purpose: a production-grade skill router AND a reference implementation for the `context.collect` hook pattern.\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:30:| **Plugin developers** | Reference implementation for `context.collect` + prompt contribution pattern. Demonstrates embedding infrastructure in an extension. |\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:37:US2: As a plugin developer, I want a reference implementation of the `context.collect` hook pattern for skill routing so I can build similar plugins without breaking system prompt caching.\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:66:- **Extension only** — no core changes to WednesdayAI. Uses existing `context.collect` hook + `api.config`.\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:85:The plugin injects retrieved skill descriptions into the **conversation** (not the system prompt) via the `context.collect` lifecycle hook — the same seam `memory-lancedb` uses for auto-recall. This preserves the system prompt's full cacheability while delivering query-relevant skill content exactly where the agent needs it: alongside the user's message.\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:88:1. `context.collect` fires with the clean user message\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:124:│  api.on(\"context.collect\", handler)                   │\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:135:context.collect event { cleanUserMessage, messages, envelope }\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:174:// Returned from context.collect handler\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:260:### D1 — `context.collect` hook for injection (irreversible: contract)\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:262:**Choice:** Use `context.collect` hook to inject skill descriptions, not `before_prompt_build`.\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:264:**Rationale:** `context.collect` returns `PromptContribution` with `prependContext` blocks, which land in the conversation portion — not the system prompt. This preserves the system prompt cache (Anthropic ephemeral, OpenAI `prompt_cache_key`). `before_prompt_build` returns a `systemPrompt` string that replaces the entire system prompt, which would vary per-query and destroy the cache hit for the full ~15K token system message.\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:268:**ADR:** [ADR-0001](/dev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md)\ndocs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:327:| Hook registration | `context.collect` handler registered on `api.on()`, fires on agent run |\ndev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md:5:title: \"ADR-0001: Use context.collect hook for skill injection\"\ndev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md:10:# ADR-0001: Use `context.collect` hook for skill injection\ndev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md:18:2. **`context.collect`** — returns a `PromptContribution` with `prependContext`, `appendContext`, `appendAfterUserMessage`, and other blocks that land in the *conversation* portion, not the system prompt.\ndev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md:22:Use `context.collect` hook for skill injection. Do not use `before_prompt_build`.\ndev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md:34:If we inject skill content into the conversation (via `context.collect`'s `prependContext`), the system prompt stays identical across requests → full cache hit. The conversation portion is dynamic anyway — adding 500–1500 tokens of skill descriptions has zero marginal caching penalty.\ndev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md:42:The `memory-lancedb` extension already uses this pattern: it reads the user message, searches a vector DB for relevant memories, and injects them as `prependContext` via `context.collect`. SkillWeaver follows the same architecture: search → inject as conversation context.\ndev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md:49:- **Negative:** The `context.collect` hook does not receive the final assembled system prompt — we can't inspect whether the user actually has `skills: \"names\"` set at runtime. We must check `api.config` at startup instead.\ndev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md:54:This returns `prependContext` (not `systemPrompt`), which also lands in conversation. But the hook signature bundles `systemPrompt` override capability, creating a footgun risk (future maintainer uses `systemPrompt` return, breaks caching). `context.collect` has no `systemPrompt` return — it's impossible to accidentally break caching.\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-r1-codex.md:14:| Medium | 016/018 | `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-6/016-lifecycle.md:130-136`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/018-integration-tests.md:87-93`, `:174-179` | Task 016 adds a second `api.on(\"agent_end\", ...)` hook, but task 018 still asserts `api.on` was called exactly once. Its own STOP trigger later allows `agent_end`, so the integration task conflicts with its dependency. | Update task 018 to assert only allowed hook names are registered: `context.collect` and `agent_end`; do not use `toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1)`. |\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-judge-codex-judges-gemini.md:14:| Critical | 016 | `index.ts:register` | **Control-flow grounding:** Teardown logic (`index.dispose()`) is wired to the `agent_end` hook. Since `agent_end` fires per agent session/run, the global singleton index is permanently destroyed after the first query, breaking all subsequent requests. | Hook teardown into `plugin_unload` (or the gateway's global lifecycle equivalent) instead of `agent_end`, or do not destroy singletons during transient events. |\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-r1-gemini.raw.log:3:  \"response\": \"I have analyzed the spec, plan, task files, and ADRs. Here is the adversarial review report:\\n\\n```markdown\\n| Severity | Task | File:Line | Issue | Remediation |\\n|---|---|---|---|---|\\n| Critical | 010 | `src/decomposer.ts:extractJsonArray` | **Fidelity mismatch:** Contradicts ADR-0003 format contract. The ADR mandates returning a JSON object (`{ \\\"subTasks\\\": [\\\"task\\\"] }`) for reliable parsing, but the prompts explicitly instruct \\\"ONLY a JSON array\\\" and parsing expects a raw array, breaking the standardized prompt contract. | Update `buildSADPass1Prompt` and `Pass2` to request `{ \\\"subTasks\\\": [...] }` and modify `extractJsonArray` to extract the `subTasks` property from the parsed object. |\\n| High | 010 | `src/decomposer.ts:decompose` | **Fidelity mismatch:** Fails to implement poor-retrieval fallback. ADR-0003 explicitly requires: \\\"If hints < 3 ... include a generic fallback: 'If no skill matches...'\\\". The implementation unconditionally uses hints without the fallback string, risking severe model hallucination on out-of-domain queries. | Add logic in `decompose()` to check `if (hints.length < 3)` and append the required fallback sentence to the prompt. |\\n| Critical | 001/002 | `src/config.ts:DEFAULTS` | **Control-flow/Crash:** `embedding.dimensions` is unconfigurable. `CloudEmbedding` hardcodes 1536. If a user sets `cloudModel` to a 3072-dim model (e.g., `text-embedding-3-large`), `hnswlib` initializes at 1536 and hard-crashes with a C++ segmentation fault when fed 3072-dim vectors. | Expose `dimensions` as a configurable property, or dynamically initialize `hnswlib` length from the first embedded vector's actual length. |\\n| Critical | 015 | `src/handler.ts:createCollectHandler` | **Hollow test / Missing logic:** Task 015 adds an `AbortSignal` to `Decomposer` but `handler.ts` NEVER passes a signal to `decompose()`. If the LLM API hangs, the agent hangs forever. The test only asserts `Promise.race` externally, making it hollow. | Wrap `opts.decomposer.decompose()` calls in `handler.ts` with `AbortSignal.timeout(5000)` and pass the signal. |\\n| High | 017 | `src/__tests__/benchmark.ts:computeCatR` | **Hollow metric:** `computeCatR` uses `expected.some()`. A multi-task query expecting 5 distinct skills passes CatR@10 if just 1 expected skill is retrieved, artificially inflating scores and completely violating SC1's per-sub-task requirement. | Calculate a strict recall ratio (`expected.filter(s => topK.includes(s)).length / expected.length`) and average across queries. |\\n| Critical | 016 | `index.ts:register` | **Control-flow grounding:** Teardown logic (`index.dispose()`) is wired to the `agent_end` hook. Since `agent_end` fires per agent session/run, the global singleton index is permanently destroyed after the first query, breaking all subsequent requests. | Hook teardown into `plugin_unload` (or the gateway's global lifecycle equivalent) instead of `agent_end`, or do not destroy singletons during transient events. |\\n| High | 009 | `src/skill-index.ts:watch` | **Bug:** Missing recursive flag. Implements `fs.watch(dir)` without `recursive: true`. Since skills live in subdirectories (`/skills/github/SKILL.md`), changes to skill files will be silently ignored on Linux/Windows, breaking the live-reload feature. | Add `recursive: true` to the `fs.watch` options object. |\\n| High | 002 | `src/config.ts:DEFAULTS` | **Fidelity mismatch:** Violates spec constraint: \\\"defaults to agent's own model\\\". Task 002 hardcodes `\\\"openrouter\\\"` and `\\\"qwen/qwen2.5-7b-instruct\\\"` as absolute defaults, bypassing the local host agent and risking unintended data leakage to a 3rd party. | Set default decomposer `provider`/`model` to `null` and resolve against `api.config.agents.defaults.model` at runtime. |\\n\\nFINDINGS: 8\\nThese findings survive peer review because they cite explicit, undeniable contradictions between the architecture documents (ADR-0003, Spec constraints) and the planned implementation, highlight native C++ crashing edge cases, and expose fundamentally hollow tests and control flow bugs that will cause production failures.\\n```\\n\\n*(Note: As I am currently operating in a sandbox Plan Mode that restricts write access to your primary codebase directories, I have output the report here. You can copy this content directly to `/Users/david/Code/WednesdayAI-plugins/docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-r1-gemini.md`)*\",\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/018-integration-tests.md:23:import type { OpenClawPluginApi } from \"wednesdayai/plugin-sdk\";\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/018-integration-tests.md:27:function createMockApi(overrides: Partial<OpenClawPluginApi> = {}): OpenClawPluginApi {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/018-integration-tests.md:37:  } as unknown as OpenClawPluginApi;\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/018-integration-tests.md:40:let plugin: { id: string; register: (api: OpenClawPluginApi) => void };\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/018-integration-tests.md:53:    it(\"registers context.collect hook\", () => {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/018-integration-tests.md:56:      expect(api.on).toHaveBeenCalledWith(\"context.collect\", expect.any(Function));\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/018-in