cs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-r1-codex.raw.log:19:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_9\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\"rg -n \\\\\\\"diffs|plugin-skillweaver|skillweaver|context.collect|sad-prompt|Embedding|embedding|register\\\\\\\" . -g '\\\"'!node_modules'\\\"' -g '\\\"'!docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-r1-*'\\\"'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"./README.md:25:    index.ts         # Plugin entry: export default { register(api) { ... } }\\n./dev-docs/workstreams/plugin-skillweaver/README.md:5:workstream: plugin-skillweaver\\n./dev-docs/workstreams/plugin-skillweaver/README.md:10:  spec: docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md\\n./dev-docs/workstreams/plugin-skillweaver/README.md:15:# plugin-skillweaver\\n./dev-docs/workstreams/plugin-skillweaver/README.md:25:- [Spec](/docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md)\\n./dev-docs/workstreams/plugin-skillweaver/README.md:26:- [ADR-0001](/dev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md) — `context.collect` hook for skill injection\\n./dev-docs/workstreams/plugin-skillweaver/README.md:27:- [ADR-0002](/dev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md) — Pluggable embedding backend interface\\n./dev-docs/workstreams/plugin-skillweaver/README.md:28:- [ADR-0003](/dev-docs/adr/0003-sad-prompt-contract.md) — SAD prompt contract and response format\\n./dev-docs/workstreams/plugin-skillweaver/README.md:34:| 0001 | `context.collect` hook for skill injection | accepted |\\n./dev-docs/workstreams/plugin-skillweaver/README.md:35:| 0002 | Pluggable embedding backend interface | accepted |\\n./dev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md:4:workstream: plugin-skillweaver\\n./dev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md:5:title: \\\"ADR-0001: Use context.collect hook for skill injection\\\"\\n./dev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md:10:# ADR-0001: Use `context.collect` hook for skill injection\\n./dev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md:18:2. **`context.collect`** — returns a `PromptContribution` with `prependContext`, `appendContext`, `appendAfterUserMessage`, and other blocks that land in the *conversation* portion, not the system prompt.\\n./dev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md:22:Use `context.collect` hook for skill injection. Do not use `before_prompt_build`.\\n./dev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md:34:If we inject skill content into the conversation (via `context.collect`'s `prependContext`), the system prompt stays identical across requests → full cache hit. The conversation portion is dynamic anyway — adding 500–1500 tokens of skill descriptions has zero marginal caching penalty.\\n./dev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md:42:The `memory-lancedb` extension already uses this pattern: it reads the user message, searches a vector DB for relevant memories, and injects them as `prependContext` via `context.collect`. SkillWeaver follows the same architecture: search → inject as conversation context.\\n./dev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md:49:- **Negative:** The `context.collect` hook does not receive the final assembled system prompt — we can't inspect whether the user actually has `skills: \\\"names\\\"` set at runtime. We must check `api.config` at startup instead.\\n./dev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md:54:This returns `prependContext` (not `systemPrompt`), which also lands in conversation. But the hook signature bundles `systemPrompt` override capability, creating a footgun risk (future maintainer uses `systemPrompt` return, breaks caching). `context.collect` has no `systemPrompt` return — it's impossible to accidentally break caching.\\n./dev-docs/adr/0003-sad-prompt-contract.md:4:workstream: plugin-skillweaver\\n./dev-docs/adr/0003-sad-prompt-contract.md:107:### Embedding the hints directly (no Pass-2 prompt)\\n./dev-docs/adr/0004-in-memory-index-no-persistence.md:4:workstream: plugin-skillweaver\\n./dev-docs/adr/0004-in-memory-index-no-persistence.md:45:- **Positive:** Dimension-agnostic — if the user switches embedding backends (384-dim → 1536-dim), the index rebuilds automatically with the new dimensions. A persisted index would need dimension-aware invalidation.\\n./dev-docs/adr/0004-in-memory-index-no-persistence.md:47:- **Negative:** Cloud embedding backends pay API cost on every rebuild. At 200 skills × $0.02/1K tokens (OpenAI ada-002 pricing), rebuild costs ~$0.002. Negligible.\\n./dev-docs/adr/0004-in-memory-index-no-persistence.md:51:### Persist to ~/.openclaw/skillweaver/index.bin\\n./dev-docs/adr/0004-in-memory-index-no-persistence.md:54:### Persist embeddings only, rebuild index from cached embeddings\\n./dev-docs/adr/0004-in-memory-index-no-persistence.md:55:Store the embedding vectors as JSON, rebuild hnswlib index from them on load. Similar complexity to full persistence. Rejected for same reason.\\n./dev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md:4:workstream: plugin-skillweaver\\n./dev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md:5:title: \\\"ADR-0002: Pluggable embedding backend interface\\\"\\n./dev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md:10:# ADR-0002: Pluggable embedding backend interface\\n./dev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md:14:The SkillWeaver plugin needs to embed skill names and descriptions into vectors for similarity search. Users have diverse embedding infrastructure:\\n./dev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md:18:- Some self-host embeddings via Infinity, Ollama, or similar Docker services\\n./dev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md:22:Define an `EmbeddingBackend` interface with three concrete implementations selected by config. The interface is:\\n./dev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md:25:interface EmbeddingBackend {\\n./dev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md:36:2. **`cloud`** — OpenAI `/v1/embeddings` API. Defaults to `text-embedding-3-small` (1536-dim). Requires API key.\\n./dev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md:37:3. **`custom`** — Any OpenAI-compatible `/v1/embeddings` endpoint. User provides URL, model name, optional API key.\\n./dev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md:51:The default is local (`all-MiniLM-L6-v2`) because it requires zero configuration — no API keys, no endpoints, no network. It works immediately. The paper validates this exact model. Users who want higher accuracy can switch to cloud (OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small`) which has a better embedding quality at the cost of API latency + cost.\\n./dev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md:55:Users running Infinity, Ollama, or other OpenAI-compatible embedding servers can point the plugin at their local endpoint. No new code path — just a different URL. This covers the \\\"Infinity in Docker with all-MiniLM-L6-v2\\\" use case without adding Infinity-specific code.\\n./dev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md:60:- **Positive:** Interface is small enough that adding a 4th backend (e.g., Gemini embedding, Cohere) is a single file.\\n./dev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md:61:- **Negative:** Different backends produce different-quality embeddings for the same text. The benchmark suite must validate all three backends independently.\\n./dev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md:67:Simpler, but excludes users who prefer cloud embeddings or self-host embedding servers. Rejected — the paper itself uses cloud embeddings for some experiments; local-only is unnecessarily restrictive.\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:5:workstream: plugin-skillweaver\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:23:This plugin brings SkillWeaver to WednesdayAI as a community extension, serving dual purpose: a production-grade skill router AND a reference implementation for the `context.collect` hook pattern.\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:30:| **Plugin developers** | Reference implementation for `context.collect` + prompt contribution pattern. Demonstrates embedding infrastructure in an extension. |\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:37:US2: As a plugin developer, I want a reference implementation of the `context.collect` hook pattern for skill routing so I can build similar plugins without breaking system prompt caching.\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:39:US3: As an infrastructure operator, I want to choose my embedding backend (local/cloud/custom) so I can optimize for cost, latency, privacy, or existing self-hosted infrastructure.\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:58:### 3 embedding backends\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:59:SC6: Pluggable embedding — Plugin works with at least three embedding backends: local (all-MiniLM-L6-v2 via @xenova/transformers), cloud (OpenAI text-embedding-3-small), custom (arbitrary OpenAI-compatible endpoint, e.g. Infinity in Docker). → US1: US3:\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:66:- **Extension only** — no core changes to WednesdayAI. Uses existing `context.collect` hook + `api.config`.\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:67:- **Skill index built at startup** — embedding index constructed in `register()`, updated on skill file changes via fs watch (debounced).\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:71:- **External dependency ceiling** — max 3 new npm deps (embedding lib, vector index, maybe an MCP SDK for skill catalog query).\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:85:The plugin injects retrieved skill descriptions into the **conversation** (not the system prompt) via the `context.collect` lifecycle hook — the same seam `memory-lancedb` uses for auto-recall. This preserves the system prompt's full cacheability while delivering query-relevant skill content exactly where the agent needs it: alongside the user's message.\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:88:1. `context.collect` fires with the clean user message\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:91:4. Retrieve top-K skills per sub-task from the embedding index\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:96:- Built in `register()` at plugin startup\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:111:│                  plugin-skillweaver                   │\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:113:│  register(api)                                       │\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:116:│    │   ├─ EmbeddingBackend (local/cloud/custom)      │\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:124:│  api.on(\\\"context.collect\\\", handler)                   │\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:135:context.collect event { cleanUserMessage, messages, envelope }\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:174:// Returned from context.collect handler\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:178:      id: \\\"skillweaver:route\\\",\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:179:      source: \\\"plugin-skillweaver\\\",\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:208:    \\\"skillweaver\\\": {\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:218:      \\\"embedding\\\": {\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:221:        \\\"cloudModel\\\": \\\"text-embedding-3-small\\\", // cloud model (OpenAI)\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:239:### Embedding backend interface\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:242:interface EmbeddingBackend {\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:252:- `LocalEmbedding` — @xenova/transformers with all-MiniLM-L6-v2 (80MB, runs in-process)\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:253:- `CloudEmbedding` — OpenAI embeddings API (text-embedding-3-small or user-specified)\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:254:- `CustomEmbedding` — any OpenAI-compatible `/v1/embeddings` endpoint (Infinity, Ollama, etc.)\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:256:Backend selection happens at `register()` time based on config. The index builder is backend-agnostic.\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:260:### D1 — `context.collect` hook for injection (irreversible: contract)\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:262:**Choice:** Use `context.collect` hook to inject skill descriptions, not `before_prompt_build`.\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:264:**Rationale:** `context.collect` returns `PromptContribution` with `prependContext` blocks, which land in the conversation portion — not the system prompt. This preserves the system prompt cache (Anthropic ephemeral, OpenAI `prompt_cache_key`). `before_prompt_build` returns a `systemPrompt` string that replaces the entire system prompt, which would vary per-query and destroy the cache hit for the full ~15K token system message.\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:268:**ADR:** [ADR-0001](/dev-docs/adr/0001-context-collect-hook-for-skill-injection.md)\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:270:### D2 — Pluggable embedding backend (irreversible: interface contract)\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:272:**Choice:** Abstract embedding behind a `EmbeddingBackend` interface with three implementations (local, cloud, custom).\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:274:**Rationale:** Users have diverse infrastructure. Some run everything locally (no API keys), some use cloud providers, some self-host embeddings via Infinity/Ollama in Docker. The interface is a thin abstraction — `embed(strings) → vectors` — that any backend can satisfy. The paper uses all-MiniLM-L6-v2 (384-dim), but higher-dimensional models (text-embedding-3-small: 1536-dim) may improve retrieval. The hnswlib index is dimension-agnostic.\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:276:**ADR:** [ADR-0002](/dev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md)\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:286:**ADR:** [ADR-0003](/dev-docs/adr/0003-sad-prompt-contract.md)\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:288:### D4 — Metadata-only embedding\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:292:**Rationale:** The paper shows metadata-only retrieval achieves CatR@10 of 69.0% (vs 70.3% with body-aware, a 1.3pp difference). The 99% context reduction already achieved by not dumping full bodies into the prompt. Embedding full bodies would inflate the index size and embedding cost with negligible accuracy gain for the retrieve-then-rerank pipeline.\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:319:| `EmbeddingBackend` (×3) | Local: loads model, embeds text, correct dimensions. Cloud: sends correct API request format. Custom: handles endpoint URL and auth. |\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:326:| All 3 embedding backends | Same skill set, same query, results within tolerance across backends |\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:327:| Hook registration | `context.collect` handler registered on `api.on()`, fires on agent run |\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:332:| Error resilience | Embedding backend down → gracefully skip routing, don't crash agent run |\\n./docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:353:- Embedding backend times out → catch, log, return empty contribution (never crash)\\n./docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-find.md:4:SPEC (FROZEN at precheck): docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md\\n./docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-find.md:5:PLAN: docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/plan.md\\n./docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-find.md:8:docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/001-plugin-scaffold.md\\n./docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-find.md:9:docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/002-config-schema.md\\n./docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-find.md:10:docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/003-register-entry.md\\n./docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-find.md:11:docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-2/004-embedding-types.md\\n./docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-find.md:12:docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-2/005-local-embedding.md\\n./docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-find.md:13:docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-2/006-cloud-embedding.md\\n./docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-find.md:14:docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-2/007-custom-embedding.md\\n./docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-find.md:15:docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-3/008-skill-index.md\\n./docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-find.md:16:docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-3/009-index-rebuild.md\\n./docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-find.md:17:docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/010-decomposer.md\\n./docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-find.md:18:docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/011-retriever.md\\n./docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-find.md:19:docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/012-context-injector.md\\n./docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-find.md:20:docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/013-collect-handler.md\\n./docs/p