sdayai-plugins/<plugin-id>`. Implementers will build the new plugin outside the repo’s plugin layout. | Rewrite all task paths, gate commands, imports, and package name to `plugins/skillweaver` / `@wednesdayai-plugins/skillweaver`, or first update the repo convention in README and make that an explicit irreversible decision. |\\n| High | 001/009/015/016 | `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/001-plugin-scaffold.md:9-15`, `:20`, `:282-285`, `:295`; `phase-3/009-index-rebuild.md:9-14`, `:18`, `:182-184`; `phase-6/015-error-resilience.md:9-15`, `:91`, `:197-199`; `phase-6/016-lifecycle.md:9-14`, `:42`, `:139-141` | Multiple tasks require creating or editing test files that are not in `files:` while `allowed_change`/Allowed moves say only listed source files may change. A strict implementer either violates the boundary or cannot make the required gate pass. | Add every required test file to each task’s `files:` list, or declare a consistent rule that `scope_test` files are allowed edits despite `files:`. |\\n| High | 005 | `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:59`, `:71`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/001-plugin-scaffold.md:78-80`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-2/005-local-embedding.md:129`, `:157-160` | SC6 requires local embeddings via `@xenova/transformers`, but the scaffold package only installs `hnswlib-node`; task 005 imports `@xenova/transformers` while its allowed files exclude `package.json`. Typecheck/runtime can fail with no permitted dependency edit. | Put `@xenova/transformers` in task 001 dependencies, or add `extensions/skillweaver/package.json` to task 005 with `allowed_change: edit`. |\\n| High | 010/012 | `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/010-decomposer.md:6`, `:198`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/012-context-injector.md:6`, `:111`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-2/004-embedding-types.md:60-103` | Tasks 010 and 012 import types created by task 004 but do not depend on 004. Scheduled literally, either task can run after 001/002 and before the type file exists. | Add `004` to `depends_on` for 010 and 012. |\\n| Critical | 008/014 | `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:95-98`, `:159-166`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-3/008-skill-index.md:4`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/014-register-wiring.md:185-187`, `:243-258` | The spec requires building an index from actual skill metadata at startup, and task 008 even says “discover skills from config”; task 014 leaves `discoverSkills()` as `return []` and explicitly says discovery is out of scope. SC1/SC2 are hollow because the live pipeline indexes zero skills. | Add a dedicated discovery task before 014, or implement real discovery in 014 using the WednesdayAI skill catalog/config paths and test that `index.build()` receives non-empty parsed skills. |\\n| Critical | 010 | `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:278-285`; `dev-docs/adr/0003-sad-prompt-contract.md:28`, `:33`, `:55`, `:58`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-4/010-decomposer.md:224-240`, `:247-269` | The irreversible SAD contract is JSON object `{ subTasks: string[] }`, but task 010 prompts for and parses a bare JSON array. This breaks the frozen decomposer protocol. | Change tests, prompts, and parser to emit/extract `{ \\\"subTasks\\\": [...] }`; keep array-only parsing only as backward-compatible fallback if explicitly allowed. |\\n| High | 004 | `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:270-276`; `dev-docs/adr/0002-pluggable-embedding-backend-interface.md:22-31`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-2/004-embedding-types.md:11`, `:65-71` | Task 004 creates the `EmbeddingBackend` interface but marks `irreversible: false`, contradicting D2/ADR-0002’s irreversible interface-contract decision. | Mark task 004 `irreversible: true` and cite ADR-0002 in the task header or body. |\\n| High | 009 | `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-3/009-index-rebuild.md:141-160` | The proposed `watch()` calls `import(\\\"node:fs\\\").watch(...)` without awaiting/importing `watch`, never assigns `this.watcher`, then returns `this.watcher`; the method returns `null` and/or typechecks incorrectly instead of starting a watcher. | Use `import { existsSync, watch } from \\\"node:fs\\\"` at top level, return `null` when the dir is missing, assign `this.watcher = watch(...)`, and close any previous watcher before replacing it. |\\n| High | 015 | `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-6/015-error-resilience.md:24-42`, `:106-119`, `:179-195` | The timeout tests are hollow: both race the unresolved implementation against an external already/soon-resolving fallback, so they pass even if `handler()`/`decompose()` never implements timeout. The change only threads an optional `signal`; no handler creates an `AbortController` or deadline. | Add a real timeout option, create/abort an `AbortController` in the handler/decomposer path, await the actual handler promise under fake timers, and assert it resolves `{}` plus passes an aborted signal to fetch. |\\n| Medium | 016/018 | `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-6/016-lifecycle.md:130-136`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/018-integration-tests.md:87-93`, `:174-179` | Task 016 adds a second `api.on(\\\"agent_end\\\", ...)` hook, but task 018 still asserts `api.on` was called exactly once. Its own STOP trigger later allows `agent_end`, so the integration task conflicts with its dependency. | Update task 018 to assert only allowed hook names are registered: `context.collect` and `agent_end`; do not use `toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1)`. |\\n| High | 017 | `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:44-47`, `:61-62`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/017-benchmark.md:432-491`, `:503-509` | The benchmark file only exports `runBenchmark`; it does not load the 50-query fixture, instantiate real or mock components, print rates, or fail when CatR@10/DA thresholds miss. The Done command can exit 0 without proving SC1, SC2, or SC7. | Add a CLI entrypoint that loads `benchmark-queries.json`, runs the real configured pipeline or deterministic benchmark mocks, prints summary, and exits non-zero unless `catR10Rate >= 0.65`, `daExactRate >= 0.60`, and latency thresholds pass. |\\n| Medium | 012 | `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:174-180`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/012-context-injector.md:49-52`, `:160-163` | The spec’s contribution source is `\\\"plugin-skillweaver\\\"`, but task 012 tests and implements `source: \\\"skillweaver\\\"`. Downstream diagnostics/filtering by source will not match the frozen contract. | Align task 012 and dependent tests to `source: \\\"plugin-skillweaver\\\"` or amend the spec before implementation. |\\n| Medium | 018 | `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-06-plugin-skillweaver.md:53-56`; `docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-7/018-integration-tests.md:70-84`, `:87-93` | The SC4 cache test sends `\\\"hi\\\"`, which is below `minQueryLength`, then only checks `systemPrompt` if the result is non-empty; it passes if no injection ever occurs. The SC5 slash-command test only checks no `before_tool_call` hook, not that `/github` or `/weather` still resolve. | Use a long query with mocked retrieval that forces `prependContext`, assert no system prompt mutation on that non-empty contribution, and add a real or SDK-level slash-command resolution fixture for representative slash commands. |\\n\\nFINDINGS: 12\\n\\nSelf-assessment: Each finding ties a concrete implementer failure to cited spec/task/repo lines and gives an applicable edit to the breakdown, not speculative implementation advice.\\n\\n\"}}\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-6/016-lifecycle.md:123:**Anchor:** add `api.on(\"agent_end\", ...)` cleanup handler inside `register()` — insert after the existing `api.on(\"context.collect\", handler)` line\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-6/016-lifecycle.md:126:    api.on(\"context.collect\", handler);\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-6/016-lifecycle.md:130:    api.on(\"context.collect\", handler);\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-6/016-lifecycle.md:132:    api.on(\"agent_end\", async () => {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-6/016-lifecycle.md:145:- `agent_end` handler throws uncaught error\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-r1-gemini.md:3:  \"response\": \"I have analyzed the spec, plan, task files, and ADRs. Here is the adversarial review report:\\n\\n```markdown\\n| Severity | Task | File:Line | Issue | Remediation |\\n|---|---|---|---|---|\\n| Critical | 010 | `src/decomposer.ts:extractJsonArray` | **Fidelity mismatch:** Contradicts ADR-0003 format contract. The ADR mandates returning a JSON object (`{ \\\"subTasks\\\": [\\\"task\\\"] }`) for reliable parsing, but the prompts explicitly instruct \\\"ONLY a JSON array\\\" and parsing expects a raw array, breaking the standardized prompt contract. | Update `buildSADPass1Prompt` and `Pass2` to request `{ \\\"subTasks\\\": [...] }` and modify `extractJsonArray` to extract the `subTasks` property from the parsed object. |\\n| High | 010 | `src/decomposer.ts:decompose` | **Fidelity mismatch:** Fails to implement poor-retrieval fallback. ADR-0003 explicitly requires: \\\"If hints < 3 ... include a generic fallback: 'If no skill matches...'\\\". The implementation unconditionally uses hints without the fallback string, risking severe model hallucination on out-of-domain queries. | Add logic in `decompose()` to check `if (hints.length < 3)` and append the required fallback sentence to the prompt. |\\n| Critical | 001/002 | `src/config.ts:DEFAULTS` | **Control-flow/Crash:** `embedding.dimensions` is unconfigurable. `CloudEmbedding` hardcodes 1536. If a user sets `cloudModel` to a 3072-dim model (e.g., `text-embedding-3-large`), `hnswlib` initializes at 1536 and hard-crashes with a C++ segmentation fault when fed 3072-dim vectors. | Expose `dimensions` as a configurable property, or dynamically initialize `hnswlib` length from the first embedded vector's actual length. |\\n| Critical | 015 | `src/handler.ts:createCollectHandler` | **Hollow test / Missing logic:** Task 015 adds an `AbortSignal` to `Decomposer` but `handler.ts` NEVER passes a signal to `decompose()`. If the LLM API hangs, the agent hangs forever. The test only asserts `Promise.race` externally, making it hollow. | Wrap `opts.decomposer.decompose()` calls in `handler.ts` with `AbortSignal.timeout(5000)` and pass the signal. |\\n| High | 017 | `src/__tests__/benchmark.ts:computeCatR` | **Hollow metric:** `computeCatR` uses `expected.some()`. A multi-task query expecting 5 distinct skills passes CatR@10 if just 1 expected skill is retrieved, artificially inflating scores and completely violating SC1's per-sub-task requirement. | Calculate a strict recall ratio (`expected.filter(s => topK.includes(s)).length / expected.length`) and average across queries. |\\n| Critical | 016 | `index.ts:register` | **Control-flow grounding:** Teardown logic (`index.dispose()`) is wired to the `agent_end` hook. Since `agent_end` fires per agent session/run, the global singleton index is permanently destroyed after the first query, breaking all subsequent requests. | Hook teardown into `plugin_unload` (or the gateway's global lifecycle equivalent) instead of `agent_end`, or do not destroy singletons during transient events. |\\n| High | 009 | `src/skill-index.ts:watch` | **Bug:** Missing recursive flag. Implements `fs.watch(dir)` without `recursive: true`. Since skills live in subdirectories (`/skills/github/SKILL.md`), changes to skill files will be silently ignored on Linux/Windows, breaking the live-reload feature. | Add `recursive: true` to the `fs.watch` options object. |\\n| High | 002 | `src/config.ts:DEFAULTS` | **Fidelity mismatch:** Violates spec constraint: \\\"defaults to agent's own model\\\". Task 002 hardcodes `\\\"openrouter\\\"` and `\\\"qwen/qwen2.5-7b-instruct\\\"` as absolute defaults, bypassing the local host agent and risking unintended data leakage to a 3rd party. | Set default decomposer `provider`/`model` to `null` and resolve against `api.config.agents.defaults.model` at runtime. |\\n\\nFINDINGS: 8\\nThese findings survive peer review because they cite explicit, undeniable contradictions between the architecture documents (ADR-0003, Spec constraints) and the planned implementation, highlight native C++ crashing edge cases, and expose fundamentally hollow tests and control flow bugs that will cause production failures.\\n```\\n\\n*(Note: As I am currently operating in a sandbox Plan Mode that restricts write access to your primary codebase directories, I have output the report here. You can copy this content directly to `/Users/david/Code/WednesdayAI-plugins/docs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-r1-gemini.md`)*\",\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/001-plugin-scaffold.md:71:  \"description\": \"SkillWeaver — compositional skill routing for WednesdayAI via context.collect hook\",\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/001-plugin-scaffold.md:105:  \"description\": \"Compositional skill routing: decompose queries, retrieve relevant skills, inject into context via context.collect hook.\",\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-judge-gemini-judges-codex.md:18:| Medium | 016/018 | Task 016 lines 130-136; task 018 lines 87-93, 174-179 | Task 016 adds second `agent_end` hook, but task 018 still asserts `api.on` called exactly once. | Update task 018 to assert only allowed hook names are registered. |\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/003-register-entry.md:22:import type { OpenClawPluginApi } from \"wednesdayai/plugin-sdk\";\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/003-register-entry.md:33:function createMockApi(overrides: Partial<OpenClawPluginApi> = {}): OpenClawPluginApi {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/003-register-entry.md:41:  } as unknown as OpenClawPluginApi;\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/003-register-entry.md:45:  let plugin: { id: string; name: string; register: (api: OpenClawPluginApi) => void };\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/003-register-entry.md:93:  it(\"registers a context.collect hook\", () => {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/003-register-entry.md:96:    expect(api.on).toHaveBeenCalledWith(\"context.collect\", expect.any(Function));\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/003-register-entry.md:108:import type { OpenClawPluginApi } from \"wednesdayai/plugin-sdk\";\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/003-register-entry.md:118:  register(api: OpenClawPluginApi) {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/003-register-entry.md:139:    api.on(\"context.collect\", async (_event) => {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-1/003-register-entry.md:157:- `api.on` is called with a hook name other than `\"context.collect\"`\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/reviews/tournament-find.md:28:dev-docs/adr/0001-plugin-skillweaver-context-collect.md\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/plan.md:7:(Gao 2026, arXiv:2606.18051) using the `context.collect` lifecycle hook — the same seam\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/plan.md:16:- **Phase 5** — full pipeline fires on every agent turn via `context.collect` (proves hook wiring)\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/plan.md:48:| 013 | 5 | context.collect handler | dep: 003 008 010 011 012 | conflicts: none |\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/013-collect-handler.md:4:title: Create context.collect handler — full pipeline: decompose → retrieve → inject; sub-agent filter; short query skip\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/013-collect-handler.md:290:- `context.collect` handler throws uncaught (must catch all and return `{}`)\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/014-register-wiring.md:4:title: Wire full pipeline in register() — build SkillIndex, discover skills, create Decomposer+Retriever, register context.collect handler\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/014-register-wiring.md:22:import type { OpenClawPluginApi } from \"wednesdayai/plugin-sdk\";\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/014-register-wiring.md:26:function createMockApi(overrides: Partial<OpenClawPluginApi> = {}): OpenClawPluginApi {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/014-register-wiring.md:36:  } as unknown as OpenClawPluginApi;\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/014-register-wiring.md:40:  let plugin: { id: string; register: (api: OpenClawPluginApi) => void };\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/014-register-wiring.md:47:  it(\"builds SkillIndex and registers a context.collect handler\", () => {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/014-register-wiring.md:50:    expect(api.on).toHaveBeenCalledWith(\"context.collect\", expect.any(Function));\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/014-register-wiring.md:98:import type { OpenClawPluginApi } from \"wednesdayai/plugin-sdk\";\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/014-register-wiring.md:108:  register(api: OpenClawPluginApi) {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/014-register-wiring.md:129:    api.on(\"context.collect\", async (_event) => {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/014-register-wiring.md:139:import type { OpenClawPluginApi } from \"wednesdayai/plugin-sdk\";\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/014-register-wiring.md:195:  register(api: OpenClawPluginApi) {\ndocs/plans/plugin-skillweaver/phase-5/014-register-wiring.md:241:    api.on(\"context.collect\", handler);\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
